\title{Separated space}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-12}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{(X,\mathcal{T})} be a [[gt-0002]]. Let #{U_{1}}, #{U_{2}} be open subsets of #{X}. We say #{U_{1}} and #{U_{2}} \define{Separate} #{X} if #{U_{1}\cap U_{2}=\emptyset} and #{U_{1}\cup U_{2}=X}.}

\p{In this case, we call #{U_{1}} and #{U_{2}} a \define{Separation} of #{X}.}